Earl Davis Cook (December 10, 1908  November 21, 1996) was a relief pitcher in Major League Baseball who played briefly for the Detroit Tigers during the 1941 season. Listed at 6' 0", 195lb., Cook batted and threw right-handed. He was born in Stouffville, Ontario, Canada. In one game appearance, Cook posted a 4.50 ERA with one strikeout in 2.0 innings of work. Cook died in Markham, Ontario, Canada at the age of 88. 
